= Commands =
vim -p[N] %% Opens Vim with N tabs

== New tabs ==
:tabnew %% Opens a new tab
:+tabnew %% Opens a new tab after the current one
:-tabnew %% Opens a new tab befor the current one
:0tabnew %% Opens a new tab befor the first one
:$tabnew %% Opens a new tab befor the first one
:tab split %% Opens a copy of the current file in another tab

== Close tabs ==
:tabc[lose] %% Close current tab
:tabo[nly] %% Close all tabs except current one

== Switch tabs ==
:tabn[ext] %% Go to next tab
gt %% same as above
:tabp[revious] %% Go to previous tab
gT %% same as above
:tabfir[st] %% Go to first tab
:tabl[ast] %% Go to last tab

== Move tabs ==
:tabm[ove] [N] %% Move the current tab after N tabs
:+tabmove %% Move tab to the right
:-tabmove %% Move tab to the left
:0tabmove %% Move tab before first tab
